				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Ah, wordcount, meh. The story is great, that&#8217;s what matters.</p>
<p>You&#8217;re building a legacy, I see &#8211; tiny bits of worldbuidling through these vignettes, I like it! The world you&#8217;ve introduced in the previous stories was confusing but fascinating, and I&#8217;m glad we are finding out more.</p>
<p>This is a nice step away from the intensity of the previous two. I love the tone &#8211; the grandfather and grandson perfectly captured, and the alien details fitting in with the universal way the stories are told. I love the detail of the weird creatures and their creators and the cthuloid developments &#8211; all very real with very little detail actually given. And I am impressed with the myth of the Pariah and how it&#8217;s building up.</p>
<p>Keep &#8217;em coming <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>
